# .env.local is OPTIONAL and git-ignored — use it only for personal secrets
# (e.g. the database password for CLI tools). Do NOT put NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_*
# values here: .env.local overrides BOTH .env.development and .env.production,
# which silently breaks the dev/prod split.
#
# Environment routing:
#   .env.development → dev database  (npm run dev)
#   .env.production  → prod database (npm run build, Netlify)
